-- 
Wind Beats Gas as Brazil Sells $18.1 Billion of Power Contracts

-- B y   S t e p h a n   N i e l s e n
-- 
2011-08-18T13:59:27Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-18/wind-beats-gas-as-brazil-sells-18-1-billion-of-power-contracts.html
 Brazilian wind farm developers
including Renova Energia SA and SeaWest WindPower Inc. agreed to
deliver electricity at lower rates than energy generated by
hydroelectric and natural gas plants at a government auction
yesterday for 29.1 billion reais ($18.1 billion) of power
contracts.  Developers of 44 wind farms agreed to sell power for 99.58
reais a megawatt-hour, national energy agency Empresa de
Pesquisa Energetica said yesterday in a statement. Two natural
gas plants signed contracts to deliver electricity for 103.26
reais a megawatt-hour, and an expansion to a hydroelectric
project in the Amazon signed a deal for 102 reais.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Stephan Nielsen in  Sao Paulo  at 
 snielsen8@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
